      <hedline>
        <hl1>Draft Worldwide Buys Stake in Capita</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By STUART ELLIOT</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Draft Worldwide buys majority interest in Capita Technologies, e-business services company; financial terms undisclosed (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Draft Worldwide in Chicago, part of the Interpublic Group of Companies, said yesterday that it had made another acquisition, buying a majority interest in Capita Technologies in Chicago, an e-business services company. Terms were not disclosed.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Draft Worldwide in Chicago, part of the Interpublic Group of Companies, said yesterday that it had made another acquisition, buying a majority interest in Capita Technologies in Chicago, an e-business services company. Terms were not disclosed.</p>
        <p>Capita, which has 400 employees and projected revenue estimated at $70 million from clients like Xerox, will operate as an autonomous unit of Draft. Jeff Kvam, 38, will remain president and chief executive at Capita, which is to relocate to New York.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
